Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.49,0:00:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was now Tishri, the start of a month-long festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We had just rebuilt the wall of Jehovah’s great city.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it was time to rebuild
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirituality of his chosen people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.13,0:00:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Many did not know God’s Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.30,0:00:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who better to help us gain understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.05,0:00:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,than a man who had come before me—Ezra?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.14,0:00:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . the regulations and judicial decisions of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.81,0:00:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He and other Levites read aloud
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.27,0:00:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Law of Moses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They not only read it but they explained it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.11,0:00:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,putting meaning into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.66,0:00:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As a people, we began to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.41,0:01:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,how badly we had disappointed Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.25,0:01:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by working on the Sabbath,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.25,0:01:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,offering lame sacrifices,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.80,0:01:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and divorcing our wives to marry foreign women.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.68,0:01:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurt our hearts, but by reading God’s Law,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.22,0:01:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we were learning to be Jehovah’s people again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.22,0:01:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not mourn or weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.23,0:01:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you know what displeases God,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.98,0:01:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do what pleases him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.36,0:01:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.36,0:01:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat the choice things, and drink what is sweet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.61,0:01:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and send a portion to those who have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And do not feel sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.33,0:01:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.13,0:01:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We followed Jehovah’s instructions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.55,0:01:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to observe the Festival of Booths.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.82,0:02:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent days rejoicing and giving thanks 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.36,0:02:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then on the 24th day,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.20,0:02:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we assembled to read God’s Law,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.25,0:02:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to confess our sins,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and to weep over our wrongdoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We made a binding agreement in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We resolved to obey Jehovah’s Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But some soon forgot their promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Peleth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.05,0:03:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reham,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,here’s our rent payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.43,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Put them in a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The basket is hard to carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.31,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear about Nehemiah’s latest idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the plan to repopulate Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.44,0:03:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean his ridiculous proposal to force families
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.78,0:03:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to move into the city—1 out of 10 by lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.82,0:03:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.82,0:03:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to be one who was chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t he care what this does to landholders like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.91,0:03:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So when are you supposed to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Move?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not moving anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a right to live where I choose, and so do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.72,0:03:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet, you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.05,0:04:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.05,0:04:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to join me in refusing to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.81,0:04:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.48,0:04:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the king sent Nehemiah here to rebuild the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.82,0:04:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is the governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.99,0:04:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Governors come, governors go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.03,0:04:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The king is waiting for Nehemiah to return,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and when he does, things will get back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.24,0:04:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when Nehemiah goes back,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will still be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.91,0:04:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is his will that Jerusalem be rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you would go along with Nehemiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so ungrateful?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,your rent!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham refuses to move into Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.54,0:05:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants us to support him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him Nehemiah is doing Jehovah’s will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham doesn’t understand how happy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.51,0:05:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he could be if-if he would just follow Jehovah’s direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will move if we are selected?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.89,0:05:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.31,0:05:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d rather be like Nehemiah than like Raham.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.65,0:05:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.71,0:05:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At the inauguration of the walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we filled Jerusalem with songs of praise 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and thanksgiving to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our great joy could be heard from far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.73,0:06:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When I finally returned to the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about that day often.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With what I know now, I wish I had never left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.04,0:06:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah raised up a messenger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who chronicled the things that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jerusalem during my absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,His name was Malachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.72,0:06:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,despite not being a Jew,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,still found his way into the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:06:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He utilized his Jewish family ties
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.98,0:07:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to take advantage of the other Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.82,0:07:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings you to the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.86,0:07:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, and to bring you this small gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah, you are always so generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.33,0:07:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s nothing, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm, is there nothing I can do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.17,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, since you asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s one little thing you could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me. What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, speaking of family . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.14,0:07:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When our relatives, yours and mine, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.14,0:07:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,visit from Samaria, it would be so nice
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a place to eat with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, right here in the temple, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.11,0:07:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they worship Jehovah too—often.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.99,0:07:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, well, sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.99,0:07:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A room in the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.16,0:07:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know I can’t do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, all the rooms are in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.41,0:07:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.42,0:08:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren’t some of them just storerooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.42,0:08:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are provisions for the Levites.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.34,0:08:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But can’t you clear one out for me? just one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I only need one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.84,0:08:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will Nehemiah say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.93,0:08:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is far away in Shushan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.73,0:08:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if he finds out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.48,0:08:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is going to tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.90,0:08:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.32,0:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.32,0:08:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So once again our high priest has given in to Tobiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.75,0:08:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where should I put this grain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.38,0:08:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s room here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.71,0:08:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful! I’ve got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who’s coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:08:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hurry, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.56,0:09:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Once they get out of our way, let’s, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.31,0:09:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s set the table here and then the chairs 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.65,0:09:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of along the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.32,0:09:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah, tell me, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where should we store our provisions now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now move along,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,like now, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we’ll unload here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.16,0:09:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and then like I said, chairs there, table here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How could Eliashib let anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,let alone a man like Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.80,0:09:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,take over a room for his own use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,after all that Nehemiah did
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.39,0:09:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to preserve the sacredness of the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people don’t give tithes anymore anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to go tend our own flocks and fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.56,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s of no value to serve God.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t let their wrong acts take away our joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.70,0:09:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How have we benefited from serving Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.91,0:09:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And doesn’t the scripture say:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.87,0:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take good care of your sheep”?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.71,0:10:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It also says:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.12,0:10:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“A faithful man will receive many blessings.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We must wait on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, he will straighten everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.18,0:10:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachi saw how far the people had fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Levites,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,once the proud keepers of Jehovah’s standards,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,now found themselves questioning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of their own service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Young man!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.72,0:10:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not offer a sheep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.39,0:11:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger the offering,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.31,0:11:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the bigger the blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.18,0:11:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.23,0:11:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know it’s more impressive to the neighbors, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.32,0:11:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I already have an offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, but look!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.53,0:11:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem like a nice man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So today, for you, a special price—huh?—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,hardly more than you paid for these doves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.29,0:11:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Come take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.04,0:11:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That sheep is blind!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And look at how it walks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Young man, that’s absolutely normal for this breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.59,0:11:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Law says not to offer blind, lame, or sick animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If ever I can afford to offer a sheep, it’ll be a sound one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.89,0:11:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t waste your money!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s a fine sheep at a fine price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.35,0:11:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Be practical!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.06,0:11:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it’s only a tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.65,0:11:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Temple services are not the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s as if they don’t even think about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.08,0:12:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Azubah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.67,0:12:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Azubah, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How’s Raham?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A certificate of divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to be a good wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.44,0:12:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn’t enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.69,0:12:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham sent me away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.49,0:12:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t fear, Azubah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live here with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We can all share.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.29,0:12:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.29,0:12:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn’t think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.71,0:12:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn’t give him children.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,With or without children,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:12:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,marriage is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.34,0:13:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He will never send you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.05,0:13:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a visitor last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.22,0:13:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or should I say your former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.56,0:13:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you care how you’ve hurt your innocent mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so hard-hearted?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:13:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Moses said if you find something
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.98,0:14:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,indecent with your wife, a man must write 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a certificate of divorce, hand it to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and dismiss her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If giving me no children isn’t indecent, then what is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.58,0:14:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I’m tired of living with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.75,0:14:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m marrying Gizla today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Gizla?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That Moabite girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.55,0:14:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you bind yourself with an oath and a curse
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not to take a wife from the nations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Law says: “They will turn your sons away
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.43,0:14:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“from following me to serve other gods;
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.72,0:14:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jehovah’s anger will blaze against you”!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you to counsel me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.64,0:14:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Every man must find his own joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I intend to find mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.11,0:14:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, only Jehovah can give true joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.65,0:14:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think you can give
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself more joy than he can?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.84,0:15:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,why do we treat each other so treacherously,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,profaning your covenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.53,0:15:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.28,0:15:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Say to the priests who are despising my name:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.24,0:15:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“A son honors a father, and a servant his master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.75,0:15:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“So if I am a father, where is the honor due me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I am a master, where is the fear due me?”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:15:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My good man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.61,0:16:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My good man, I see you have no offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have you Levites despised Jehovah’s name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.68,0:16:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Despised it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.51,0:16:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You present a blind, lame, or sick animal
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as a sacrifice and say that it is nothing bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.19,0:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Should Jehovah accept it from your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.31,0:16:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the meat is in our pot,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.07,0:16:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,no one can tell if it was lame or sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Jehovah? Can he tell the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.16,0:16:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,One day Jehovah will come to his temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.58,0:16:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He will cleanse you sons of Levi by fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.62,0:16:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachi, what’s gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.04,0:17:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you complain
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when everyone else approves?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘O priests, if you refuse to take it to heart,’
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.30,0:17:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“says Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I will send on you the curse,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.01,0:17:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and I will turn your blessings into curses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Return to me, and I will return to you,’ says Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed to return?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Will a mere human rob God?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.77,0:17:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you are robbing me,’ says Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How have we robbed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.07,0:17:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘In the tithes and in the contributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You are robbing me—yes, 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“the entire nation is,’ says Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.58,0:17:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Bring the entire tithe into the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘so there may be food in my house;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.29,0:17:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and test me out, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and see whether I will not open to you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.92,0:17:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘the floodgates of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and pour out on you a blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,until there is nothing lacking.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s another thing you do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he no longer looks favorably
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on anything you offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.64,0:17:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you betray the wife of your youth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,although she’s your partner, your legal wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some who don’t do that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have what remains of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So guard yourselves respecting your spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not deal treacherously
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.70,0:18:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wife of your youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I hate divorce,’ says Jehovah the God of Israel.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.20,0:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The lips of a priest should safeguard knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and people should seek the law from his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.67,0:18:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you have made many stumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.56,0:18:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s message revealed that the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was in their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.40,0:18:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In spite of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.40,0:18:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachi sought out those who found joy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing what was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Peleth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.25,0:19:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.25,0:19:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Azubah,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.54,0:19:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see the distinction
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,between the righteous and the wicked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.55,0:19:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,between one who serves God
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.01,0:19:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and one who doesn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.18,0:19:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I serve Jehovah as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can tell you that when you speak with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah, he pays attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.19,0:19:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A book is written before him of those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.44,0:19:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who fear him and meditate on his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.16,0:19:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For years, I was away from Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.72,0:20:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but my heart was always with my people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I requested to return to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I found shocked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.27,0:20:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliashib!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,May you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.81,0:20:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t expecting . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.69,0:20:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are all the Levites and the singers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.95,0:20:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are away right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.41,0:20:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Away?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.78,0:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are they away?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.54,0:20:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedaiah is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.66,0:20:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.41,0:20:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,show Governor Nehemiah around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.63,0:20:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.51,0:20:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.31,0:20:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me about the temple services.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.81,0:20:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have all the provisions that you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.02,0:20:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Governor Nehemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.02,0:20:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we have nearly no provisions at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.52,0:20:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,For a long time, the priests and the Levites
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,have not taken their duties seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.98,0:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When the people saw that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.40,0:21:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they stopped bringing in tithes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.03,0:21:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the tithes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,most Levites and singers returned to their fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have you not returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, I’m getting by.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.58,0:21:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve always believed that Jehovah helps
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,those who trust in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.88,0:21:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I know he will correct things in his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.63,0:21:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Eliashib not tell the people to bring your provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.26,0:21:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In your absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.89,0:21:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophet Malachi warned him and all the priests.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.01,0:21:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But Eliashib—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.18,0:21:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He took our storeroom and emptied it of our provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.69,0:21:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it to Tobiah to use as a dining hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.20,0:21:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedaiah, help us get rid of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.50,0:21:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.09,0:22:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliashib!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.55,0:22:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.26,0:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have you and the deputy rulers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,neglected the house of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.56,0:22:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.31,0:22:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You and they,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.10,0:22:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,please cleanse this room
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.56,0:22:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and replace the utensils.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.10,0:22:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.73,0:22:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And gather all the Levites,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.81,0:22:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the singers, and the deputy rulers to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.35,0:22:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m assigning them all back to their posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.98,0:22:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedaiah, I’m placing you, Shelemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.28,0:22:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and Zadok in charge of the storerooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.74,0:22:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanan will be your assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.28,0:22:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s your responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.70,0:22:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to distribute provisions to your brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.41,0:22:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.83,0:22:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,wait-wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.33,0:22:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.41,0:22:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will tell all Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.25,0:22:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring in the tenth of the grain,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.42,0:22:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the new wine, and the oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.63,0:22:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can explain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.21,0:22:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.27,0:22:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do remember me, O my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.86,0:23:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not wipe out my acts of loyal love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.65,0:23:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the house of my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.99,0:23:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only had they neglected Jehovah’s house
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.83,0:23:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but some of the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,continued to conduct business on the Sabbath
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.38,0:23:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—a day Jehovah had declared as holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.80,0:23:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you selling today?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.22,0:23:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the best quality fish from Tyre.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.10,0:23:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.60,0:23:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not care that this is the Sabbath?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.39,0:23:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.27,0:23:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this evil thing you’re doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.82,0:23:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why God brought disaster on this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.98,0:23:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The people think it’s acceptable now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.44,0:23:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Jehovah think?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.45,0:23:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped the buying and selling
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.49,0:23:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and ordered the doors closed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.49,0:23:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to keep the Sabbath day holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.84,0:24:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But the following week, the merchants tried again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.72,0:24:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.72,0:24:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to sleep on the ground last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.85,0:24:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know God’s Law: No work, 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.14,0:24:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,no business on the Sabbath!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.14,0:24:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You and all the Levites, guard the gates 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.19,0:24:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep the Sabbath holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.94,0:24:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t let anyone in!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.28,0:24:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This, too, remember to my credit, O my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.50,0:24:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and show me pity 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.75,0:24:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,according to your abundant loyal love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.76,0:24:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There was another thing that I had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.09,0:24:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.34,0:24:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Ana la mitbayen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.97,0:24:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.01,0:24:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to listen to me. I’m your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.77,0:24:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong with your children?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.68,0:25:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t like coming to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.19,0:25:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweetie, why don’t you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.15,0:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Shvok Y-ati!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.78,0:25:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back here now!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.07,0:25:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.08,0:25:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife speaks very little Hebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.58,0:25:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not swear never to marry someone
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.25,0:25:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn’t serve Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.71,0:25:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, nobody cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.54,0:25:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.21,0:25:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.30,0:25:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why have you ignored the command of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.17,0:25:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own oath?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.22,0:25:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.43,0:25:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder your children don’t love Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.26,0:25:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.26,0:25:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you imagine that you could succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.97,0:25:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,without Jehovah’s blessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.98,0:25:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed for Jehovah’s blessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.27,0:25:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.23,0:25:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But you didn’t obey him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.19,0:25:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, how can Jehovah bless something 
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.44,0:25:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that is against his will?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.16,0:25:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was I surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.37,0:25:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The people were just following
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.91,0:25:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the bad example of those taking the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.91,0:26:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliashib’s grandson married a Horonite,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.96,0:26:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the daughter of Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.18,0:26:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you no respect for God’s Law?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.56,0:26:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You should not give your daughters to their sons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.81,0:26:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or accept any of their daughters for your sons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.98,0:26:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.40,0:26:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it not because of these that King Solomon sinned?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.24,0:26:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandfather, say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.70,0:26:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Be still, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.70,0:26:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not something unheard of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.83,0:26:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to commit this great evil
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.96,0:26:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by marrying foreign women?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.09,0:26:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have defiled the priesthood!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.09,0:26:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not serve as a priest or remain in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.97,0:27:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.39,0:27:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll go to Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.85,0:27:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re more tolerant there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.82,0:27:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But he’s my grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.15,0:27:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did you allow him
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.15,0:27:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to disregard Jehovah’s laws?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.28,0:27:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know our temple services
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.50,0:27:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,are what preserve our relationship with God!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.33,0:27:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But as soon as I left,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.79,0:27:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.96,0:27:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you let it fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.56,0:27:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It took some time, but true worship was restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.58,0:28:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When I look back on all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.54,0:28:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah enabled us to do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.13,0:28:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the opposition we faced, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.21,0:28:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.97,0:28:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we turn the accusation of sedition
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.13,0:28:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,against Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.26,0:28:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The next sound they hear
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.18,0:28:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,will be our battle cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.77,0:28:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to wait until they start killing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.98,0:28:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . the bad influences we avoided, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.85,0:28:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a right to live where I choose, and so do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.15,0:28:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to join me in refusing to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.32,0:28:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t waste your money!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.57,0:28:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Be practical!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.86,0:28:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it’s only a tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.74,0:28:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.49,0:28:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to go tend our own flocks and fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.37,0:28:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s of no value to serve God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.41,0:28:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . the sleepless nights, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.41,0:28:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go to Jerusalem to keep an eye on Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.13,0:28:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you see? These people hate what we’re doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.46,0:28:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.13,0:28:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to live and work around them like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.05,0:28:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . the sweat and toil, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.92,0:29:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, this work is too much for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.05,0:29:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.05,0:29:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need a wall anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.72,0:29:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . I just remember the joy we felt
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.23,0:29:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because we were serving Jehovah the right way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.69,0:29:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought we were just working on a wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.11,0:29:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah was rebuilding our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.45,0:29:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never forget how Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.29,0:29:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,brought us together to accomplish his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.71,0:29:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He taught us to rely on him,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.51,0:29:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and he strengthened us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.51,0:29:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat the choice things, and drink what is sweet,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.81,0:29:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and send a portion to those who have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.23,0:29:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And do not feel sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.69,0:29:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.41,0:30:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do remember me favorably, O my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.88,0:30:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah was a man of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.26,0:30:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have stayed in the luxurious palace
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.26,0:30:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of Shushan and served Jehovah from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.52,0:30:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When a need arose,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.31,0:30:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,he was ready to make the long journey
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.82,0:30:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jerusalem to support his brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.57,0:30:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wouldn’t be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.45,0:30:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he had to ask the king of Persia to let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.20,0:30:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.20,0:30:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a courageous person for Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.37,0:30:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he rely on his personality
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.04,0:30:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or his good record with the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.42,0:30:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch this part again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.25,0:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The place where my forefathers are buried lies in ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.47,0:31:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been consumed by fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.80,0:31:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.55,0:31:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.01,0:31:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you seeking?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.31,0:31:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At once, I prayed to the God of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.94,0:31:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If it pleases the king
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.36,0:31:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and if your servant has found favor with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.82,0:31:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,send me to Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.82,0:31:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to the city where my forefathers are buried,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.12,0:31:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me rebuild it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.59,0:31:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.92,0:31:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.43,0:31:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah immediately and humbly prayed to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.47,0:31:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the true Source of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.43,0:31:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he prayed repeatedly
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.98,0:31:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout his assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.40,0:32:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah blessed his efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.15,0:32:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So lesson number one for us today:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.28,0:32:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When times are hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.90,0:32:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we may be quick to lean on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.61,0:32:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if things are going well?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.87,0:32:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we still reliant on Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.49,0:32:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or might we find ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.95,0:32:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming complacent, perhaps even saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.17,0:32:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Things are good in my life now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.71,0:32:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“I know there’s a need to get to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.76,0:32:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“but I’ve been serving Jehovah for many years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.93,0:32:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’ve done my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.05,0:32:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let someone else do it”?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.39,0:32:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Jehovah bless such an attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.68,0:32:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t it be better to turn to Jehovah in prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.77,0:32:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,asking him to give you the courage and joy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.78,0:32:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue to reach out in your service to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.36,0:32:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You just might be surprised
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.20,0:32:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at the doors Jehovah opens for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.00,0:33:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, once Nehemiah arrived in Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.12,0:33:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn’t just give orders, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.42,0:33:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says that he daily worked
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.67,0:33:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,alongside his fellow Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.51,0:33:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the break of dawn
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.34,0:33:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,until the stars came out.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.18,0:33:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.89,0:33:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when we show a self-sacrificing spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.81,0:33:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will give us the energy needed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.73,0:33:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry out the task at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.98,0:33:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Israelites completed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.86,0:33:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the wall-building project in just 52 days!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.74,0:33:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What an amazing feat,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.37,0:33:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in the face of continual opposition!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.58,0:33:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, it came in the form of mocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.46,0:33:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the opposers threatened to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There were Samaritans in the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.88,0:33:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ammonites in the east, Arabs in the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.59,0:33:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ashdodites in the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.22,0:34:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem was surrounded by enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.27,0:34:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been easy to feel trapped
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.35,0:34:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and to give in to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.48,0:34:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Nehemiah do?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.40,0:34:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was his pattern?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.78,0:34:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In his own words, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.49,0:34:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“We prayed to our God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.95,0:34:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Nehemiah strengthened the people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.45,0:34:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by telling them:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.79,0:34:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be afraid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Jehovah, who is great and awe-inspiring.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.09,0:34:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they kept building.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.38,0:34:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After Nehemiah’s enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.38,0:34:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,realized that their open threats had failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.01,0:34:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,did they give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.80,0:34:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.56,0:34:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They now turned to other forms of opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.56,0:34:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they tried three different schemes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.36,0:34:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to sidetrack Nehemiah from the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.36,0:34:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice them?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.40,0:34:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch the video again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.24,0:34:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked to meet Nehemiah halfway.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.95,0:35:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell this to Nehemiah:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.21,0:35:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.17,0:35:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and let us set a time to meet together
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.84,0:35:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Valley Plain of Ono.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.96,0:35:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to lure me away
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.63,0:35:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jerusalem to do me harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.47,0:35:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They spread false rumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.39,0:35:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, it’s time to implement your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.56,0:35:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah, write this down:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.69,0:35:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Among the nations it has been heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.15,0:35:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“and Geshem is also saying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.40,0:35:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you and the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.91,0:35:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“are scheming to rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.16,0:35:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why you are building the wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.29,0:35:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And they used a traitor to try and trick Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.17,0:35:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re coming to kill you—by night!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.09,0:35:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go into the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.05,0:35:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and close the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.55,0:35:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shemaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.34,0:35:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,should a man like me run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.51,0:36:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.47,0:36:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that do to the spirit of the entire nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.22,0:36:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the only safe place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.64,0:36:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I’m not a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.65,0:36:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I entered the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.56,0:36:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be valid reason to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.32,0:36:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.78,0:36:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That decision would be foolish, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.24,0:36:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.95,0:36:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah and Sanballat put you up to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.87,0:36:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t they, you hypocrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.00,0:36:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah remember them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.92,0:36:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of you false prophets
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.50,0:36:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who keep trying to frighten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.13,0:36:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.30,0:36:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.01,0:36:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Three schemes, three failures
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.64,0:36:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—so lesson number two:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.06,0:36:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Nehemiah, we might encounter opposers
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.73,0:36:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,who scheme to bring our loyal service to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.86,0:37:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Some may invite us to meet them halfway, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.58,0:37:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They may try to convince us that if we serve Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.91,0:37:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with just a little less zeal,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.87,0:37:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we could pursue
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.21,0:37:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,worldly goals at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.25,0:37:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, because God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.00,0:37:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,comes first in our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.22,0:37:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be like Nehemiah and refuse to compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.47,0:37:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We know where this world is headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.47,0:37:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Opposers also spread false accusations against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.06,0:37:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In some lands, we’re accused
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.23,0:37:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of posing a threat to the State.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.73,0:37:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some accusations have been successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.19,0:37:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,rebutted in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.95,0:37:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever the outcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.86,0:37:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re confident that Jehovah will direct matters
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.08,0:37:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,according to his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.83,0:37:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Opposition may also come from those
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.91,0:37:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who pretend to serve Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.42,0:37:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as a fellow Jew tried to get Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.38,0:37:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to break God’s Law to save his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.21,0:38:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so former Witnesses may try
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.88,0:38:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to get us to compromise in one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.93,0:38:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we reject apostates because we know
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.77,0:38:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that our lives are saved,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.06,0:38:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not by breaking God’s laws, but by keeping them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.03,0:38:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time, Nehemiah refused to fall into their trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.90,0:38:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.36,0:38:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he had a brilliant mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.20,0:38:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.03,0:38:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because he relied on Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.04,0:38:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah gave him the insight needed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.04,0:38:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to see through their deceptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.42,0:38:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,After the wall was built,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.51,0:38:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah left Jerusalem for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.13,0:38:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did he find on his return?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.76,0:38:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of coming back to find true worship thriving,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.85,0:38:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he found it barely surviving.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.23,0:38:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All the work that he had done
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.02,0:39:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to help the people to trust in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.53,0:39:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—how do you think he felt?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.11,0:39:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have said: “That’s it!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.95,0:39:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m out!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.57,0:39:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let someone else clean this up,” and walked away.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.49,0:39:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.83,0:39:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.79,0:39:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have you and the deputy rulers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.42,0:39:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,neglected the house of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.13,0:39:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You and they, please cleanse this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.88,0:39:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know God’s Law:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.09,0:39:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No work, no business
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.51,0:39:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Sabbath!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.05,0:39:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.35,0:39:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not swear never to marry someone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.26,0:39:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn’t serve Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.85,0:39:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why have you ignored the command of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.85,0:39:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own oath?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.61,0:39:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Eliashib’s grandson married a Horonite,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.36,0:39:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the daughter of Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.74,0:39:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You should not give your daughters to their sons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.20,0:39:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or accept any of their daughters for your sons!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.99,0:39:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You have defiled the priesthood!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.62,0:39:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not serve as a priest
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.58,0:39:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or remain in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.88,0:40:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It took some time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.71,0:40:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but true worship was restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.60,0:40:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah didn’t walk away, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.39,0:40:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he persevered in his assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.64,0:40:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.73,0:40:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he held on to his joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.11,0:40:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, his main source of joy came,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.86,0:40:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not from his accomplishments,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.90,0:40:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,not from the security of walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.57,0:40:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or even from what others were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.58,0:40:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,From where does true joy come?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.96,0:40:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah himself told us:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.83,0:40:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“The joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.84,0:40:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is lesson number three for us:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.97,0:40:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite challenges and setbacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.68,0:40:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be joyful because true joy comes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.89,0:40:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from a good relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.31,0:41:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah was a man like you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.85,0:41:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, he didn’t have Jehovah’s power
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.90,0:41:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed supernaturally to him
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.94,0:41:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like Moses and Joshua did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.24,0:41:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did he have?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.74,0:41:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He had prayer, he had faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.58,0:41:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and he had trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.16,0:41:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were his tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.29,0:41:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no doubt that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.04,0:41:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was active on behalf of Nehemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.75,0:41:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,guiding and blessing his efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.34,0:41:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We have those same tools today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.01,0:41:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to Jehovah, put faith in him,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.80,0:41:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and trust that he will bless your self-sacrificing efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.31,0:41:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Jehovah gave Nehemiah 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.31,0:41:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage, the energy, the insight, 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.77,0:41:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the perseverance to carry out his assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.07,0:41:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll do the same for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:12.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は ユダヤ人の暦では ティシュリ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.45,0:00:16.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,この月にさまざまな祭りが行われます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.62,0:00:20.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの城壁の修復は\N完了したばかりです
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:25.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし今度は エホバとの関係を\N修復しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:29.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の律法を知らない人が大勢います
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.55,0:00:31.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰が教えますか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.10,0:00:37.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々から尊敬されており\N私より長くここにいる エズラです
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:41.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,これがエホバの規定と法規です
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:44.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エズラと他のレビ族は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:47.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセの律法の書を読み聞かせました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:49.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ朗読するだけではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:53.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かりやすく説明して\N意味を教えたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.12,0:00:58.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,民は これまでの行いが\Nどれほど神を悲しませたかを
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.04,0:01:00.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,理解するようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.54,0:01:02.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日を守らないこと
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.83,0:01:06.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,足が不自由な動物の犠牲を捧げること
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.30,0:01:11.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻を離婚して他の民族の女性と\N結婚することなどです
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:15.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,心が痛みましたが \N神の律法を聞いて学び
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.68,0:01:19.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの崇拝が\Nどういうものかが分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.27,0:01:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,悲しんだり泣いたりしないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.48,0:01:25.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,何がエホバを悲しませるかが分かった今
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:28.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの喜ぶことを行いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.32,0:01:33.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,行って 良い物を食べ \Nぶどう酒を飲み
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.62,0:01:36.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,持っていない人と分け合いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,悲しんではいけません
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.45,0:01:43.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバからの喜びは\N皆さんの力となるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:55.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは仮小屋の祭りについての\Nエホバの指示に従いました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.03,0:02:14.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の祝福に感謝する\N喜ばしい日々を過ごしました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.83,0:02:18.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,その月の24日には
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.16,0:02:21.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の律法を聞くために集まり
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.71,0:02:23.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪を告白し
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:27.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い行いについて泣き悲しみました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.93,0:02:39.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 書面で厳粛な誓約をしました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.07,0:02:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは エホバの律法に従うことを\N心に決めたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.79,0:03:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,アーメン！アーメン！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:08.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもすぐにそれを忘れた人もいました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.09,0:03:10.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペレト！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:13.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.01,0:03:18.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月の家賃分だ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.06,0:03:21.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,袋に入れろよ 運びにくいだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:27.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤが言ったこと聞いたか？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.90,0:03:29.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムに住むって話？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.94,0:03:33.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ くじで選ばれた家族が\N移住させられる
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.65,0:03:35.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ばかげた話だ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.66,0:03:38.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ 聞いてる
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.70,0:03:40.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,うちが選ばれたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.95,0:03:45.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしてだ？俺は地主だぞ\Nおかしいだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.96,0:03:48.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,へえ！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.25,0:03:50.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでいつ引っ越すの？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:53.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,引っ越す？俺は行かないぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.84,0:03:57.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,好きな所に住む権利がある そうだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:03:59.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,うちは選ばれなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.72,0:04:03.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かんないぞ\N選ばれたら おまえも断るんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.90,0:04:07.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.52,0:04:13.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは王の指示で\N再建のために来た
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.82,0:04:16.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは総督だぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.82,0:04:20.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうせ総督は代わる\Nネヘミヤはシュシャンに帰る
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:23.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいつがいなくなれば\Nまた好きなようにできる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:28.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえネヘミヤがいなくなっても\Nエホバは見ておられる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.54,0:04:31.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの再建はエホバの指示だ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:34.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,信じてないのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.59,0:04:37.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤの肩ばかり持ちやがって
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.47,0:04:39.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,俺はどうなるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:44.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.56,0:04:48.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,忘れ物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:01.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,何話してたの？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.79,0:05:05.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハムはエルサレムに\N引っ越すのを嫌がってる
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:10.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕にも行くなと
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:12.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは何て言ったの？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.80,0:05:17.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはエホバに\N従ってるって言ったんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.64,0:05:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに従えば幸せになれるのに
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.97,0:05:24.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハムはそれが分かってない
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:30.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,うちも 選ばれたら引っ越すの？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:34.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:37.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤに倣いたい
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:40.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハムじゃなくて いいよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.99,0:05:42.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:05:44.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.79,0:05:54.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁の奉献式の日
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:59.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムは神への感謝と\N賛美の歌であふれました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:07.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びの声ははるか遠くにまで\N響き渡りました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.48,0:06:14.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,シュシャンに戻ってからも\Nこの時のことをよく思い返しました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:21.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも まだエルサレムを\N離れるべきではなかったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 私が去った後
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.47,0:06:39.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムで起きた事を\N記録させるため
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.13,0:06:41.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人物を用います
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:44.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはマラキです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:50.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,トビヤを覚えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.35,0:06:52.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼はユダヤ人ではありませんでしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:55.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿に出入りし
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:57.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人との姻戚関係を利用して
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:01.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分勝手に行動していました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.70,0:07:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここに来るのは久しぶりだな\Nどうした？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:06.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたにお会いしたくて
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.54,0:07:10.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああこれ つまらないものですが
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.75,0:07:14.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,トビヤ いつもすまないね
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.13,0:07:16.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,とんでもありません
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.80,0:07:19.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ 今日は何かな？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:23.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,じゃあ1つ頼んでもいいですか
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:25.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 何だい？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.68,0:07:27.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええっと 家族のことなんですが・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.77,0:07:29.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:33.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,私とあなたの親族が\Nサマリアから訪ねて来たとき
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:36.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に食事できる場所が\Nあればいいと思って
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.11,0:07:37.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,うーん
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.36,0:07:40.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう この神殿の中に
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.45,0:07:44.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしたら彼らもしょっちゅう\Nエホバを崇拝できますよね
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.99,0:07:47.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや まあ 時々かな
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.66,0:07:49.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿の中に？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.71,0:07:52.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,無理なのは知ってるだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:56.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 空き部屋もない
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:07:59.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,空き部屋がない？貯蔵室は？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:03.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこはレビ族の食糧置き場だ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.22,0:08:06.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つくらい使わせてくださいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.89,0:08:09.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,1部屋 1部屋だけ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.85,0:08:12.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤが何と言うか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:15.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,何を恐れているんですか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:17.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはシュシャンですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.99,0:08:20.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも万が一
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.03,0:08:22.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,告げ口する人がいるんですか\Nまさかあなたが？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.99,0:08:24.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや そんな！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.66,0:08:27.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,なら 問題はない
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.97,0:08:43.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,大祭司はまたトビヤの言いなりか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:46.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこに置けばいいですか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.56,0:08:48.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここに 気を付けて
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:50.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,はーい
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.02,0:08:54.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,見ろ 来たぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.78,0:09:00.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,早くしてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:04.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,物がなくなったら \Nテーブルを・・・ここに
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.45,0:09:07.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして椅子は\N壁沿いに置いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.37,0:09:10.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,トビヤ ここにあったものは\Nどこに持っていけばいいですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:14.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,知りませんよ 好きにすればいいでしょ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.38,0:09:18.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,とにかく さっさとどいてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:21.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,で・・・ 椅子はここでいいと
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.05,0:09:23.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,テーブルはこんなふうに・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:25.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして食糧はこの辺りに\N置いていただけますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.72,0:09:28.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブは何を考えているんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:31.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,個人的な目的で部屋を\N使ってはいけないはずだ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:34.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ましてトビヤはユダヤ人でもない
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:37.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,せっかくネヘミヤが神殿を\N神聖なものとしてくれたのに
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:40.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,レビ族のための寄付も\Nほとんどされていない
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:44.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,畑や羊の世話をしないと\N食べていけないし
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:47.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えてる意味が分かんない
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.03,0:09:50.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たち
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.41,0:09:52.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びを失うべきじゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.79,0:09:56.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕だけで\N食べていけないんですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:10:01.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 自分の「羊をよく\N世話しなさい」って書いてある
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.30,0:10:07.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 「忠実な人は多くの\N祝福を受け［る］」とも書いてある
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.89,0:10:10.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを待たなきゃ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:14.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,いずれエホバが全てを正してくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.19,0:10:19.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキは人々がエホバを\N軽んじているのを見ました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:23.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,かつては律法を守ることを\N誇りにしていたレビ族までが
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.61,0:10:27.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では自分たちの奉仕に\N疑問を抱いています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.19,0:10:56.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,お兄さん！
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.44,0:10:59.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,羊持っていかない？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.23,0:11:03.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,供え物が大きいと 祝福も大きいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:09.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに ご近所にもいい顔ができる
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.37,0:11:12.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫 もうありますから
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.41,0:11:14.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,待って 待って
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.41,0:11:17.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう お兄さんいい人そうだから
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:20.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別にお安くしとくよ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.13,0:11:24.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ このハトより安いくらい\Nちょっと見ていきなって
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.38,0:11:28.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,その羊は目が見えてない\N歩き方も変だ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:33.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,いやいや この品種ではこれが普通だよ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.10,0:11:37.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法には欠陥のある動物を\N捧げてはいけないと書いてある
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.94,0:11:40.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし羊を買えるんだったら\N傷のないものにするさ！
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:43.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,お買い得なのに\N品物もいいし 値段もいい
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.82,0:11:45.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,もういいから
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:49.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢くいこうよ！\Nそんなの ただの伝統だろ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:51.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ！
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.62,0:11:55.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿は変わってしまった
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.37,0:11:59.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのことなんて みんな考えてない
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:05.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,アズバ！
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:07.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうした？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.59,0:12:10.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,何があった？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:15.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハムは？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.61,0:12:26.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,離婚証書？！
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.61,0:12:30.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,私 いい妻でいるように頑張ったわ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.95,0:12:33.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも駄目だったみたい
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.96,0:12:38.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,家を追い出された
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.17,0:12:42.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫だ アズバ\Nここにいればいい 一緒に
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:44.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうよ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.96,0:12:48.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああもう 私のせいだわ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.05,0:12:50.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなふうに考えないで
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:53.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの人の子を産めなかったから
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.93,0:12:59.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚の絆に \N子供がいるいないは関係ない
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.06,0:13:04.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信じて\N絶対に見捨てられない
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:11.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとう
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.77,0:13:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム！
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:41.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,昨日 うちに誰が来たと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.23,0:13:46.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,君の妻
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.03,0:13:51.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや「元」妻と言った方がいいのかな
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.33,0:13:57.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,何の落ち度もないのに\N離婚するなんてひどいじゃないか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:14:01.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセも言っただろ\N妻に恥ずべき点があれば
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:06.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,離婚証書を手渡し\N家から去らせろって
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.21,0:14:09.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,俺の子を産まなかったのは\N立派な理由になる
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:13.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,それにもうあいつには飽きたんだ\N今日ギズラと結婚する
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:15.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギズラ？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.77,0:14:17.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,モアブ人の？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.06,0:14:22.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの民族の女性と\N結婚しないって誓ったよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:24.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法にはこうある
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.69,0:14:28.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「彼らはあなたの息子を\Nほかの神々に仕えさせる・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.07,0:14:30.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時エホバの怒りが燃え」るって！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.53,0:14:33.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,俺に意見するつもりか？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.41,0:14:36.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の幸せは自分で決める
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.00,0:14:41.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム 人を幸せにできるのは\Nエホバだけだ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:46.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の力で幸せになれるって\N本気で思ってるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:09.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ どうしてですか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.74,0:15:12.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが互いに裏切り
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.28,0:15:15.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,契約を汚しているのは
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:26.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキ！
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.13,0:15:31.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の名を軽んじている\N祭司たちに言いなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.09,0:15:37.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,「子は父を敬い 召し使いは主人を敬う
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.06,0:15:39.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が父であるのなら
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.68,0:15:43.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,私への敬意はどこにあるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.35,0:15:45.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が主人であるのなら
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:49.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,私への畏れはどこにあるのか」
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.79,0:16:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いらっしゃい
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.37,0:16:04.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,供え物はいかがですか おっ！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.86,0:16:31.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜレビ族はエホバの名を\N軽んじているんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:34.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,軽んじている？どういうことだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.03,0:16:38.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなた方は \N欠陥のある動物を捧げながら
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.87,0:16:40.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いことではないと言っている
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.95,0:16:42.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは受け入れられるだろうか？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:47.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,肉になってしまえば\N傷物かどうかなんて分からないさ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.13,0:16:51.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうか エホバにも\N分からないと思うか？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.47,0:16:53.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつの日かエホバが神殿に来て
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:56.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,金や銀のようにあなた方を\N精錬するでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:58.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキ いいかげんにしろ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:03.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが受け入れていることに\N言い掛かりをつけるな
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:05.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは言われました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:08.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,「祭司たちよ あなたたちが\N心に留めないなら
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.82,0:17:11.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたたちに災いをもたらし
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.28,0:17:14.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちの祝福を災いに変える
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.53,0:17:17.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,私のもとに戻ってきなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:20.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 私も\Nあなたたちのもとに戻ろう」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.08,0:17:22.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,戻るとはどういうことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:25.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神から奪うことなど\Nあり得ないと思うか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.75,0:17:28.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちは奪っている」と\Nエホバは言われました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.50,0:17:30.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,奪っている？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:32.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,「10分の1や寄進物のことである」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:35.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「国民全体が私から奪っている
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:40.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,10分の1全部を持ってきて\N私の家に食物があるようにしなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.77,0:17:42.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が天の水門を開いて
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.81,0:17:45.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,あふれるほどに祝福を注ぐかどうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.35,0:17:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,私を試してほしい」とも言われました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:55.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 神が犠牲を受け入れられない\Nほかの理由もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:17:57.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは何だ？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.28,0:18:01.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなた方は若い時からの\N妻を裏切っています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.20,0:18:04.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし そうしない人もいました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.96,0:18:08.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が残っていたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:12.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の内面の傾向に気を付けなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:16.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い時からの妻を裏切ってはいけません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.26,0:18:20.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は離婚を憎む」と\Nエホバは言われました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:23.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司の唇は知識を保つべきであり
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.48,0:18:26.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,民は祭司の口に律法を求めるべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.60,0:18:31.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,なのに あなた方は多くの人の\N信仰を妨げています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.45,0:18:42.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキに与えられたエホバの言葉は
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.12,0:18:46.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題が人々の心にあることを\N明らかにしました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:52.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでもマラキは 正しいことを\N行いたいと思う人たちを探しました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:03.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペレト
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.43,0:19:05.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:10.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,アズバ 元気を出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.15,0:19:13.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんは正しい人と悪い人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:17.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に仕える人と仕えない人の\N違いを目にすることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.03,0:19:20.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,さすが 預言者だわ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.12,0:19:22.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたと同じエホバの奉仕者です
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.91,0:19:25.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんがエホバについて語り合う時
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.00,0:19:28.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは耳を傾けておられます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.88,0:19:31.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は ご自分を畏れる人たちのことを
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.79,0:19:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,記録の書に記されます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.92,0:19:40.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが共におられますように
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.32,0:19:55.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は何年もエルサレムを離れていました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそこの人たちのことは\N忘れませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.66,0:20:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで王からエルサレムに\N戻る許可をもらいます
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.45,0:20:07.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも戻ってきて 衝撃を受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.25,0:20:09.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブ！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.42,0:20:11.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに平和がありますように
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.42,0:20:13.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:15.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ど どうしてここに・・・？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:18.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,レビ族と歌い手たちはどこですか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.18,0:20:20.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと出掛けてて・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.30,0:20:24.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,出掛けてる？ どういうことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.06,0:20:28.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ・・・ あっ ペダヤ ペダヤ！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.44,0:20:31.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤをご案内して
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:36.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ ちょっと失礼していいですか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:38.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああどうぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.33,0:20:46.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペダヤ 神殿での奉仕はどうですか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:49.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,食糧は足りていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.17,0:20:51.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどありません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.13,0:20:57.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,長いこと祭司とレビ族は\N務めを果たしていません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.51,0:21:01.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを見て人々は10分の1を\N納めなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.51,0:21:05.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで祭司たちは畑仕事に\N戻ってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.64,0:21:08.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは残ったんですね？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.56,0:21:11.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい あるもので何とかやっています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.15,0:21:14.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは信仰を持つ者を\N決してお見捨てになりません
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.40,0:21:17.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが必ず事態を正されるはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.65,0:21:21.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブは 食糧を持ってくるよう\N人々に言わなかったのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:24.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが留守の間 マラキが\Nエルヤシブと祭司たちに
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.66,0:21:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,警告を与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:29.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエルヤシブは
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:32.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,食糧の置かれていたこの部屋を
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.17,0:21:36.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,食堂としてトビヤに使わせています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.43,0:21:51.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペダヤ 手伝ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:21:59.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,何をしている？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.82,0:22:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブ！あなたこそ何をしている
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.49,0:22:07.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして神の家を\Nないがしろにしているのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.33,0:22:08.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:11.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなでこの部屋を清め\N全て元に戻しなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.33,0:22:12.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,おっしゃる通りに
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.92,0:22:16.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てのレビ族と歌い手たち\N代官たちを集めなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.13,0:22:18.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなを持ち場に戻らせます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.26,0:22:22.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペダヤ シェレムヤとザドクと一緒に\N貯蔵室を見てください
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.59,0:22:24.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハナンが手伝います
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.64,0:22:26.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちに食糧を分けてください
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.01,0:22:30.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ 待ってください\N説明しますから
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.85,0:22:33.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから ユダの人たちに
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.40,0:22:38.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,穀物と新しいぶどう酒と油の\N10分の1を持ってくるように伝えます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.32,0:22:40.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.95,0:22:42.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,待って
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.33,0:22:57.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ覚えていてください
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.80,0:23:03.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の家のために私が示した\N揺るぎない愛を
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.35,0:23:12.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの家がないがしろに\Nされていただけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.06,0:23:16.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが神聖なものとして\N定めた 安息日に
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:19.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,商売をしている人もいました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.78,0:23:24.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は何があるの？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.95,0:23:28.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,おいしい魚だ\Nティルスのね
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:33.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,何をしているのですか\N今日は安息日です
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.33,0:23:35.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:40.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日を汚すとは何事ですか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.67,0:23:42.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからこの町は滅ぼされたんです！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.67,0:23:44.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,今じゃみんなやってます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.47,0:23:46.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはどう思う
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.39,0:23:49.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は商売をやめさせ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.68,0:23:54.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日を神聖なものとするために\N扉を閉じさせました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.90,0:24:06.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 次の週も\N商人たちはやってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.07,0:24:09.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,一体どういうつもりだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.08,0:24:11.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,昨日は野宿したんだぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.54,0:24:13.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法を知ってますよね
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.54,0:24:16.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日には仕事も商売もしてはいけない
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.88,0:24:21.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰りなさい！安息日を神聖なものと\Nするために見張ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.96,0:24:24.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰も入れてはいけません
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.56,0:24:36.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ どうかこのことも覚えていて
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.85,0:24:41.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,私に揺るぎない愛と\N思いやりを示してください
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.61,0:24:47.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題はほかにもありました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.95,0:24:49.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,おいで
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.78,0:24:51.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,Ana la mitbayen
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.91,0:24:56.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,戻ってきなさい！\Nお父さんの言うことを聞くんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.62,0:24:58.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたんですか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.71,0:25:01.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿に行きたがらないんです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.30,0:25:05.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえ？どうして嫌なの？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.34,0:25:07.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,Shvok Y-ati!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.34,0:25:09.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,待ちなさい！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.93,0:25:17.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,すいません 妻が\Nヘブライ語を話さないので
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.23,0:25:22.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは エホバに仕えていない人と\N結婚しないと誓いましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.15,0:25:25.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ もう昔の話です
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.65,0:25:27.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,何言ってるんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.20,0:25:28.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かった 分かった！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.53,0:25:31.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ エホバの命令と\N自分の誓約を軽んじるのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.83,0:25:33.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,放してくれ！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.62,0:25:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,親がこれじゃ子供はエホバを愛せない
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.08,0:25:40.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの祝福なしに\N成功できるとでも思うのか！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.38,0:25:42.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,祝福は祈り求めている！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.42,0:25:45.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうか！でも神に従っていない
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.26,0:25:51.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラハム 律法に反する結婚を\Nエホバが祝福するはずがない
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.85,0:25:54.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはある意味仕方のないことでした
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.48,0:25:57.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々を教え導く立場の人たちが
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.39,0:25:59.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い手本を示していたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.02,0:26:03.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブの孫はベト・ホロンの人と\N結婚しています
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.40,0:26:06.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンバラテの娘です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.08,0:26:18.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして律法を不敬に扱うのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.54,0:26:21.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の民族の娘を
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.92,0:26:25.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちの息子や自分のために\N迎えてはなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.76,0:26:28.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの王ソロモンは
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.80,0:26:32.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことで罪を\N犯したのではありませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.39,0:26:36.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か言ってよ おじいちゃん
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.39,0:26:38.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,黙っていなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.27,0:26:41.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の民族の女性と結婚することなど
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.11,0:26:45.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,あってはならない神に対する\N大きな罪です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.86,0:26:52.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは祭司職を汚しています
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.70,0:26:57.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司を辞めて\Nエルサレムから出ていきなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.08,0:27:04.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かった じゃあサマリアに行く
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.01,0:27:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここは窮屈だ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.64,0:27:13.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれは私の孫だ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.81,0:27:18.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではなぜ 黙って見ていたのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.56,0:27:23.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との良い関係を保つには\N神殿での奉仕が不可欠です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.36,0:27:25.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,知っていますよね
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.49,0:27:29.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,それなのにあなたたちは
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.11,0:27:31.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,私がここにいない間
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.57,0:27:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちがすべきことを\Nしていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.46,0:27:47.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間はかかりましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.47,0:27:51.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,再び真の崇拝が\N行われるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.98,0:28:10.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,今思えば エホバはいつも力を\N与えてくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.03,0:28:15.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ反対に遭っても・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.79,0:28:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,いい考えがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.87,0:28:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤを反逆の罪で\N訴えるのはどうでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.29,0:28:25.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうなったら攻め込むしかないだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.25,0:28:28.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺されるまで待ってろと言うのですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.13,0:28:30.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,良くない影響にさらされても・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.51,0:28:34.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,好きな所に住む権利がある そうだろ\N選ばれたら おまえも断るんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.93,0:28:39.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,お買い得なのに 賢くいこうよ！\Nそんなの ただの伝統だろ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.89,0:28:43.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,畑や羊の世話をしないと\N食べていけないし
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.27,0:28:45.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えてる意味が分かんない
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.44,0:28:47.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,眠れない夜も・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.48,0:28:50.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムに行こう\Nネヘミヤから目を離すな
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.32,0:28:54.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,やつらは俺たちのやってることが\N気に食わないんだ 分からないんですか
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.16,0:28:56.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も知らないくせに！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.20,0:28:58.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕事がきつくても・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.20,0:29:00.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに仕事が多過ぎる もうへとへとだ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.66,0:29:03.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,そもそも何で城壁が必要なんだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:08.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな中でも 正しい方法で\Nエホバに仕えていた私たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.01,0:29:11.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びに満たされていました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.34,0:29:17.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはただ城壁を建て直している\Nと思っていましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.93,0:29:23.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちの信仰を\N建て直してくださっていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.90,0:29:29.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがご自分の目的を\N成し遂げるために
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.11,0:29:31.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを集めてくださったことを
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.90,0:29:35.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は決して忘れないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.87,0:29:39.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは ご自分に頼るよう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.75,0:29:43.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを教え 強めてくださったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.00,0:29:47.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い物を食べ ぶどう酒を飲み
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.80,0:29:50.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,持っていない人と分け合いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.63,0:29:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,悲しんではいけません
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.80,0:29:57.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバからの喜びは\N皆さんの力となるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.44,0:30:09.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の神 私のことをどうか覚えていて
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.61,0:30:13.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,恵みを与えてくださいますように
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.58,0:30:26.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤには勇気がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.38,0:30:28.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,快適なシュシャンの宮殿にとどまり
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:31.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこでエホバに仕えることも\Nできましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.51,0:30:33.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうはしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.63,0:30:36.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要が生じた時\N兄弟たちを助けるために
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.01,0:30:40.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムへの長旅をすることを\Nいといませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.27,0:30:43.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそれは簡単ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.81,0:30:47.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず ペルシャの王の許可が必要でした
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.48,0:30:51.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤが勇気を出して王に話すのに\N何が助けになったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.99,0:30:56.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の能力や王との\N良い関係に頼ったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.41,0:30:59.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,この部分をもう一度見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.41,0:31:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムが荒れ果て 門も焼け落ちて\Nしまっていると聞いたので・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.50,0:31:07.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだったのか・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.84,0:31:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでおまえはどうしたいと\N思っているんだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.42,0:31:15.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに天の父に祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.76,0:31:22.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし私が
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.68,0:31:25.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の好意を得ており
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.02,0:31:29.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が良いと思われるのでしたら
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.32,0:31:34.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,私をユダに行かせ\Nそこを再建させてください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.70,0:31:41.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,行きなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.83,0:31:44.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは祈りに答えてくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.50,0:31:50.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは すぐにそして謙遜に
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.80,0:31:54.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気を下さる方エホバに祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.42,0:31:56.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後も繰り返し祈りつつ働き
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.97,0:32:00.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはその努力を祝福されました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.93,0:32:03.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで最初の教訓です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.35,0:32:07.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは 苦しい時には\Nエホバに頼るかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.48,0:32:10.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも問題が何もない時はどうですか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.73,0:32:14.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような時にも\Nエホバに頼るでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.57,0:32:17.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなふうに考えるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.53,0:32:20.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分は今の生活に満足している
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.08,0:32:25.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで長年エホバにお仕えしてきた
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.25,0:32:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,やるべきことがたくさんあるのは\N分かっているけど
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.33,0:32:31.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の分は十分果たした
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.50,0:32:34.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,後はほかの人にやってもらおう」
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.51,0:32:39.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこのような態度を\N喜ばれるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.72,0:32:45.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,「もっと奉仕を続けることができるよう\N勇気と喜びを与えてください」と
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.35,0:32:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈り求める方が\N良いのではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.94,0:32:57.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっとエホバは 思いも寄らない\N奉仕の機会を開いてくださるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.99,0:33:01.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて エルサレムに到着したネヘミヤは
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.49,0:33:05.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々に指示を出すだけでは\Nありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.87,0:33:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書によれば ネヘミヤは毎日
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.17,0:33:11.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「夜明けから星が出る頃まで」
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.59,0:33:15.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間のイスラエル人たちと\N一緒に働きました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.63,0:33:20.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが同じように\N自己犠牲の精神を示す時
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.68,0:33:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちにも\N必要な力を与えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.81,0:33:32.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエル人は わずか52日で\N城壁を完成させました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.61,0:33:35.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,さまざまな反対の中での再建工事は
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.40,0:33:38.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさに偉業と言えます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.03,0:33:42.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対者たちは最初\Nあざけるだけでしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.45,0:33:46.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて実力行使に出ると言って\N脅してきます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.37,0:33:50.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時のエルサレムは 北にサマリア人
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.67,0:33:54.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,東にアンモン人 南にアラビア人
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.25,0:33:57.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして西にアシュドドの人たちと
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:34:00.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵に囲まれていました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.18,0:34:04.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,八方ふさがりと思える状況でした
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.93,0:34:08.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,この局面でネヘミヤはどうしましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.44,0:34:12.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,やはり「神に祈り」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.56,0:34:16.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 「彼らのことを\N恐れてはなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.99,0:34:20.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,偉大で威厳に満ちる\Nエホバがおられることを
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.07,0:34:24.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,忘れないでください」と言って\N皆を励ましました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.49,0:34:30.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁再建の作業が\N止まることはありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.79,0:34:34.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵たちは 自分たちの脅しが\N効かなかったことを知って
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.96,0:34:37.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,引き下がりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.42,0:34:41.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ 別の手を使いました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.76,0:34:45.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤに城壁の再建をやめさせるため
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.18,0:34:48.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つの巧妙なわなを仕掛けました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.27,0:34:51.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,覚えておられますか？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.40,0:34:53.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオを見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.40,0:34:59.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず ネヘミヤを町の外に\Nおびき出そうとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.95,0:35:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤにこう伝えろ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.87,0:35:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「オノの谷あいの平原の村で会おう」
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.12,0:35:14.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,私をエルサレムからおびき出すつもりだ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.55,0:35:20.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に 根も葉もないうわさを流しました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.38,0:35:24.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゲシェム あの手で行くしかないな
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.26,0:35:27.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,トビヤ 書いてくれ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.35,0:35:34.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「周りの民族の間で\Nあなたのことがうわさになっている
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.31,0:35:36.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゲシェムも言っていたが
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.44,0:35:40.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたとユダヤ人は\N反逆をもくろんでいる
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.45,0:35:44.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから城壁を建て直している」
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.74,0:35:49.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 裏切り者を使ってネヘミヤを\Nわなにはめようとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.62,0:35:52.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,やつらが殺しに来る 今夜だ！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.96,0:35:55.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿に逃げ込んで 扉を閉めるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.84,0:35:59.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェマヤ 総督である私が逃げるのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.09,0:36:01.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなこと言ってる場合じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.09,0:36:04.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや 私がそんなことをしたら\Nみんなはどう思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.14,0:36:06.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,安全な場所はそこしかない
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.14,0:36:09.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 私は祭司でもない
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.48,0:36:12.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿に入ることは許されていない
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.48,0:36:14.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は入らない！
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.31,0:36:18.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,俺の言う通りにするんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.99,0:36:25.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうか
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.03,0:36:28.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,トビヤとサンバラテの差し金か
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.91,0:36:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,この裏切者！
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.96,0:36:36.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 敵たちと あなた方\N偽預言者たちを処罰される
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.79,0:36:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,行こうハナニ 仕事に戻ろう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.39,0:36:47.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵は 3回わなを仕組みましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.35,0:36:50.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,3回とも失敗します
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.43,0:36:53.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここから2つ目の教訓が得られます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.81,0:36:56.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも ネヘミヤのように
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:36:59.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵たちからの妨害を受けるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.86,0:37:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,その1つは 私たちを\N妥協させようとするわなです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.74,0:37:09.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば エホバへの奉仕の手を\N少し緩めれば
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.83,0:37:13.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,この世界で成功できると言う人がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.67,0:37:18.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし私たちは 神の王国を\N第一にした生活をしているので
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.59,0:37:20.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,妥協はしません
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.21,0:37:25.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,この世界がどこに向かっているかを\N知っているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.68,0:37:31.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,また敵たちは 根も葉もない\Nうわさを広めます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.68,0:37:37.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある国では 私たちが国家を脅かす\N存在だと非難されています
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.90,0:37:40.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,裁判で私たちが勝訴した例もありますが
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.03,0:37:43.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな結果になるとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.07,0:37:47.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが物事を導いてくださることを\N確信できます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.03,0:37:53.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エホバに仕えているふりをする\N人たちからの攻撃もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.62,0:37:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,命を守るため ネヘミヤに神の律法を\N破るよう唆したユダヤ人がいたように
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.75,0:38:03.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,偽兄弟たちは 私たちが\N何かの点で妥協するよう
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.88,0:38:06.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,わなを仕組んでくるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.76,0:38:09.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも 命が救われるためには
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.72,0:38:11.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の律法を破るのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.81,0:38:15.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを守る必要があることを\N私たちは知っているので
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.39,0:38:18.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような背教者たちを退けます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.07,0:38:22.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,結局 ネヘミヤはわなに\Nはまりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.03,0:38:25.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.07,0:38:27.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭が良かったからでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.53,0:38:29.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうことではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.12,0:38:32.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもエホバに頼ったので
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.50,0:38:38.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが彼に敵の策略を見抜く\N洞察力をお与えになったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.09,0:38:41.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁再建の後
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.17,0:38:45.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはしばらくの間\Nエルサレムを離れました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.72,0:38:49.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,戻ってきた時 そこは\Nどうなっていましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.64,0:38:54.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の崇拝は 嘆かわしい\N状態にありました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.23,0:38:59.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで すでに一生懸命\N働いてきたネヘミヤは
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.19,0:39:01.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように考えましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.03,0:39:04.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私はもう十分にやった
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.86,0:39:09.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,後は 誰かに任せよう」と言って\N投げ出すこともできたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.24,0:39:12.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そうはしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.79,0:39:14.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.87,0:39:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして神の家を\Nないがしろにしているのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.04,0:39:21.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなでこの部屋を清め\N全て元に戻しなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.71,0:39:23.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法を知ってますよね
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.71,0:39:27.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日には仕事も商売もしてはいけない
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.05,0:39:29.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰りなさい！
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.05,0:39:34.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは エホバに仕えていない人と\N結婚しないと誓いましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.56,0:39:38.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ エホバの命令と\N自分の誓約を軽んじるのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.90,0:39:42.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブの孫は\Nベト・ホロンの人と結婚しています
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.78,0:39:45.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンバラテの娘です
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:52.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の民族の娘をあなたたちの息子や\N自分のために迎えてはなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.79,0:39:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは祭司職を汚しています
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.04,0:39:59.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司を辞めて\Nエルサレムから出ていきなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.42,0:40:02.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間はかかりましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.46,0:40:06.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,再び真の崇拝が\N行われるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.05,0:40:14.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは最後までやり抜きました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.22,0:40:16.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそうできたのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.06,0:40:20.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びがあったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.61,0:40:24.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤの喜びの一番の理由は
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.07,0:40:28.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁を完成させたという達成感でも
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.16,0:40:32.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁があるという安心感でも
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.49,0:40:35.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの人の行動でもありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.79,0:40:39.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ自身こう述べています
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.75,0:40:44.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバからの喜びは\N皆さんの力となるのです」
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.38,0:40:48.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 3つ目の教訓です
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.63,0:40:51.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな試練や障害があっても
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.30,0:40:55.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びの一番の理由は\Nエホバとの良い関係にあるので
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.89,0:40:58.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは幸せでいられます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.69,0:41:01.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは私たちと同じ\N不完全な人間です
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.94,0:41:06.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,また モーセやヨシュアが見たような\N奇跡を見ることもありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.07,0:41:11.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ネヘミヤが成功したのは\Nどうしてですか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.28,0:41:14.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈り エホバを信じ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.83,0:41:17.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに頼ったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.62,0:41:21.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エホバご自身が\Nネヘミヤのために行動し
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.50,0:41:26.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,その努力を導き 祝福されたことに\N疑問の余地はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.26,0:41:30.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりの日に住む私たちも同じです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.84,0:41:34.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈り エホバを信じ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.31,0:41:36.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに頼りましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.56,0:41:39.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは必ず祝福してくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.06,0:41:44.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤに 勇気 力 洞察力
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.82,0:41:47.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,粘り強さを与えたエホバは
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.15,0:41:51.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたのことも必ず\N支えてくださるでしょう
